Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

48ec1fba-b861-4be4-b44a-279bfeec8e3c.description=
Synopsis

    This flow wraps low-level HPOO getters and then makes a list of data centers available for consumption by future groups.
    callAtlasGetterByDataCenter performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the UUID for the provided flow NAME\: $getterOperation.
      2. Get the required inputs based on the UUID/getterOperation.
      3. Pull list of clusterNames from Vantive/OCI via the $dataCenter input.
      4. Iterate through clusters\: load inputs, launch the getterOperation, and then document either the success and output or the failure.
      5. Output all pass and failed clusters, outputs, or both.
      6. Respond with Unknown for any failed flows.


Inputs

    getterOperation - Low-level command found in (/Library/HostingEngineering/Library/StorageFlows/NetApp) -- getUUID -- to run publically against all clusterNames (required).
	Valid Values\:
	Default Value\:


   dataCenter - dataCenter to run against (as of 11/15/13, hardcoded.  OCI/Mule callback may one day translate dataCenter\=clusterNamesList)
	  Valid values\: Any current Savvis/CL active Data Center with Atlas NetApp Clusters
	  Default value\: None.
	  
  <*> - Any and all other loaded inputs, will be "overloaded* and used by the getterOperation called. Example would be siteID
	  Valid values\: Valid inputs to the target flow, and inputs.
	  Default value\: None.

Results

    callAtlasGettersOutput - Output of target flow (getterOperation)

Responses

    Success - Ran against all clusterNames successfully, returns cluster-aware data from each NetApp.
    Failure - Failure to run getterOperation against clusterName.
    Unknown - Return Non-Zero\: Most cases for issue with one or more clusterNames connectivity and retrieval within Data Center, or couldnt find UUID of getterOperation.

Notes

     1. Example Input from Cordys\:

         
            atlas
            48ec1fba-b861-4be4-b44a-279bfeec8e3c
            false
            
                
                  getterOperation
                  blah
                  
                
                  dataCenter
                  SL7
                  
                
                  siteId
                  S1110
